388
00:29:41,220 --> 00:29:44,100
Your rabbit flew to heaven

389
00:29:44,140 --> 00:29:45,540
to be with the Moon Goddess.

390
00:29:46,460 --> 00:29:47,460
Why did my rabbit

391
00:29:47,500 --> 00:29:49,380
go to another woman?

392
00:29:50,260 --> 00:29:52,180
You adults always lie.

393
00:29:52,660 --> 00:29:53,780
She’s gone.

394
00:29:54,260 --> 00:29:55,460
She didn’t go to heaven.

395
00:29:56,380 --> 00:29:57,700
My rabbit is dead.

396
00:29:58,380 --> 00:29:59,740
I’ll never be able to see her again

397
00:30:02,180 --> 00:30:03,500
just like I lost my father forever

398
00:30:05,180 --> 00:30:06,820
after he died.

399
00:30:08,340 --> 00:30:10,500
Nobody would go to heaven.

400
00:30:10,980 --> 00:30:13,180
That’s a lie. Not true at all!

401
00:30:34,060 --> 00:30:34,780
Yes.

402
00:30:36,300 --> 00:30:37,260
The deceased

403
00:30:37,580 --> 00:30:38,860
won’t come back to life.

404
00:30:40,300 --> 00:30:42,660
Things like they’ll still watch us aren’t true.

405
00:30:44,260 --> 00:30:45,460
They won’t even show up

406
00:30:45,460 --> 00:30:46,500
in our dreams.

407
00:30:47,860 --> 00:30:49,060
But what can we do?

408
00:30:55,100 --> 00:30:56,420
After your rabbit died,

409
00:30:57,580 --> 00:30:58,980
you could take revenge.

410
00:31:00,580 --> 00:31:01,700
That’s good.

411
00:31:31,850 --> 00:31:41,480
♪ Loved you a gentleman yet got abandoned ♪

412
00:31:42,880 --> 00:31:51,300
